etymologies: late 18th century: from modern Latin Gracula, from Latin graculus ‘jackdaw’

definitions: a songbird of the American blackbird family, the male of which has shiny black plumage with a blue-green sheen.

notes.text: Several genera and species, family Icteridae, in particular the common grackle (Quiscalus quiscula)

shortDefinitions: songbird of American blackbird family, male of which has shiny black plumage with blue-green sheen

definitions: another term for an Asian mynah or starling, with mainly black plumage.

notes.text: Gracula and other genera, family Sturnidae; southern grackleis another term for grackle (see mynah)

shortDefinitions: another term for Asian mynah or starling
